cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on planning and control of legged robots, specifically a quadrupedal robot walking on a dynamic platform. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper presents a model-based controller for tracking planned trajectories during quadrupedal walking on a dynamic platform, and also includes stability analysis for the closed-loop hybrid dynamical system. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): Although not explicitly mentioned, optimization techniques used for motion planning may involve machine learning algorithms. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): Similar to cs.LG, optimization techniques used for motion planning may involve AI algorithms. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although not the main focus of the paper, computer vision may be used for perception and sensing in legged locomotion on dynamic platforms.
